knowledge.question: When working with the stack in Assembly, which of the following are correct?
choices: The stack grows from low memory addresses to high memory addresses
The stack memory addresses are randomly selected by the OS
The stack grows from high memory addresses to low memory addresses
The stack is a first in first out memory structure
explanation: A stack uses a linear set of memory addresses and work as a last in, first out order (LIFO) utilizing from high to low memory addresses within the allocated stack.
